Step 1: Calculate the Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities (only current liabilities are given) = 4,319,436.82  
• Total Owner's Equity = 29,290,835.16  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity =  
  4,319,436.82 / 29,290,835.16 ≈ 0.1476 → approximately 0.15

Step 2: Calculate the Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 1,290,835.16  
• Total Revenue = 16,388,736.33  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (1,290,835.16 / 16,388,736.33) × 100 ≈ 7.88%

Step 3: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –6,316,405.44  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 4,319,436.82  
• Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities  
  = –6,316,405.44 / 4,319,436.82 ≈ –1.4628 → approximately –1.46

Now, presenting the answer in the required JSON format:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.15",
    "Net Profit Margin": "7.88%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-1.46"
  }
}
